Package com.cafean.CalcServer.jobrpc

Class JobRPCResponder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.rpc.AbstractRPCConnection
      • com.cafean.rpc.RPCResponder
        • com.cafean.CalcServer.rpc.AbstractServerResponder
          • com.cafean.CalcServer.jobrpc.JobRPCResponder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable
    public class JobRPCResponder
extends AbstractServerResponder
    The custom responder object used by the Calculation Server to interact directly with jobs. This class encapsulates all communication with the job from the server side. This includes methods for each RPC call.

    All RPC methods in this class that do not return an RPCResponse may return RPCResponse.COMM_FAILURE to indicate that the connection failed during the request and could not be re-established.

      • createCallback

        public CallbackNotifier createCallback​(CallbackAuthorization auth,
                                       RPCResponder oldResponder)
        Description copied from class: RPCResponder
        Creates a callback notifier for the given authorization and responder. Note that the authorization has already been verified at the time that this method is called.

        This base implementation creates a base CallbackNotifier with a LinkedList of PibBlocks as the Queue.

        Sub-class implementations may choose to use a custom notifier extension and/or a custom Queue extension, or both.

        Overrides:
        createCallback in class RPCResponder
        Parameters:
        auth - the CallbackAuthorization identifying the callback
        oldResponder - the RPCResponder to convert into a callback notifier
        Returns:
        a CallbackNotifier created from the given responder
